subSubSection.paragraph:
Median lobe of aedeagus (
Fig. 8G
) in ventral view laterally parallel; apex subtriangular, slightly rounded, with generally elongate median tooth; ventral surface with a shallow median depression at apical third; in lateral view median lobe clearly and regularly curved in basal ¾s and straight in apical ¼; dorsal ligula short – from apical third to apical part of median lobe of aedeagus –, wide, apically thinner. Spermatheca (
Fig. 11F
) with pyriform basal part; collum moderately elongate, about twice as long as apical part; ductus elongate, thickset, apically inserted.

Widespread in Northern, Central and Southern Grande Terre (
Fig. 14A
).
